SIMPLE: fawn
RECORDS: 5

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fawn
<hw>Fawn</hw> <pr>(f⟦add⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>faon</ets> the young one of any beast, a fawn, F. <ets>faon</ets> a
fawn, for <ets>fedon</ets>, fr. L. <ets>fetus</ets>. See
<er>Fetus</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A young deer;
a buck or doe of the first year. See <er>Buck</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The young of an animal; a whelp.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[The tigress] . . . followeth . . . after her
<qex>fawns</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A fawn color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fawn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fawn
<hw>Fawn</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of the color of a fawn;
fawn-colored.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fawn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Fawn
<hw>Fawn</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>faonner</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To bring forth a fawn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fawn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Fawn
<hw>Fawn</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Fawned</conjf> <pr>(f⟦add⟧nd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Fawning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>fawnen</ets>,
<ets>fainen</ets>, <ets>fagnien</ets>, to rejoice, welcome, flatter, AS.
<ets>f⟦ae⟧gnian</ets> to rejoice; akin to Icel. <ets>fagna</ets> to
rejoice, welcome. See <er>Fain</er>.]</ety> <def>To court favor by low
cringing, frisking, etc., as a dog; to flatter meanly; -- often followed
by <ptcl>on</ptcl> or <ptcl>upon</ptcl>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You showed your teeth like apes, and <qex>fawned</qex> like
hounds.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou with trembling fear,⟦br⟧
Or like a <qex>fawning</qex> parasite, obeyest.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Courtiers who <qex>fawn</qex> on a master while they betray
him.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fawn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Fawn
<hw>Fawn</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A servile cringe or bow; mean
flattery; sycophancy.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fawn-colored</ent>⟦br⟧
